    {
      "id": "pFwAARunTloTKmeL9pkEx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 570.58203125,
      "y": 1568.2578125,
      "width": 723.7998046875,
      "height": 1225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 186384638,
      "version": 147,
      "versionNonce": 569734398,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774706385021,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why We Need Redux\n\n1. Centralized State Management\n2. Predictable State Updates\n     - State changes only through:\n     - Actions → Reducers\n     - Makes behavior predictable and traceable\n\n3. Easy Debugging:\n    You know:\n        - What changed (action)\n        - When it changed\n        - Why it changed\n\n4. Avoid Prop Drilling:\n    Instead of:\n        App → A → B → C → D\n    \n    Component D → Store\n\n5. Better State Sharing\n    Multiple components can use same data:\n        - user info\n        - auth state\n        - cart items\n        - bookings\n\n6. Scales Well for Large App:\n    Redux is useful when:\n        - App has many components\n        - State is shared globally\n        - Logic becomes complex\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why We Need Redux\n\n1. Centralized State Management\n2. Predictable State Updates\n     - State changes only through:\n     - Actions → Reducers\n     - Makes behavior predictable and traceable\n\n3. Easy Debugging:\n    You know:\n        - What changed (action)\n        - When it changed\n        - Why it changed\n\n4. Avoid Prop Drilling:\n    Instead of:\n        App → A → B → C → D\n    \n    Component D → Store\n\n5. Better State Sharing\n    Multiple components can use same data:\n        - user info\n        - auth state\n        - cart items\n        - bookings\n\n6. Scales Well for Large App:\n    Redux is useful when:\n        - App has many components\n        - State is shared globally\n        - Logic becomes complex\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "n-WffjYatq3wDr6eIr0MK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 549,
      "y": 2774.3828125,
      "width": 846.999755859375,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 916279550,
      "version": 19,
      "versionNonce": 1671582882,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774696600781,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In Short: \n\nRedux is used to manage global state in a centralized, \npredictable, and scalable way, avoiding prop drilling \nand making debugging easier.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In Short: \n\nRedux is used to manage global state in a centralized, \npredictable, and scalable way, avoiding prop drilling \nand making debugging easier.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
